data.chText: 每年的；一年一次的；年度的
data.enText: happening or done once every year

data.chText: 年会；一年一度的大事；年度报告

data.enText: relating to a period of one year

data.chText: 年收入；年度订阅费；年度预算

data.enText: an average annual growth rate of 8%
a book, especially one for children, that is published once a year, with the same title each time, but different contents

data.chText: 一年生植物；一季生植物
data.enText: any plant that grows and dies within one year or season

simple_means.memory_skill: annu 年，一年 + al …的 → 一年一度的

tr: a reference book that is published regularly once every year
(botany) a plant that completes its entire life cycle within the space of a year
completing its life cycle within a year
example: a border of annual flowering plants

example.ex: ...the annual conference of Britain's trade union movement...
In its annual report, UNICEF says at least 40,000 children die every day.
example.tran: 在其年度报告中，联合国儿童基金会称每天至少有4万名儿童死亡。

example.ex: Companies report to their shareholders annually.
example.tran: 各公司每年向其股东汇报一次。

value.def: Annual quantities or rates relate to a period of one year.

example.tran: 每年的花销、学费和各项杂费6,600英镑。

example.ex: The electronic and printing unit has annual sales of about $80 million.
example.tran: 电子印刷部门每年销售额约为8,000万美元。

example.ex: El Salvador produces 100,000 tons of refined copper annually...
example.tran: 萨尔瓦多每年生产10万吨纯铜。

example.ex: Holiday World hires 300 new employees annually.
example.tran: 假日世界每年雇佣300名新员工。

value.def: An annual is a book or magazine that is published once a year.

example.ex: I looked for Wyman's picture in my high-school annual...
example.tran: 我在中学年刊中寻找怀曼的照片。

example.ex: He tried the various almanacs, annuals and gazettes which were held in the library.
example.tran: 他试着在图书馆里找过各种历书、年鉴和报纸。

value.def: An annual is a plant that grows and dies within one year.

example.ex: The simplest way to deal with these hardy annuals is to sow them where they are to flower.
example.tran: 处理这些一年生耐寒植物最简单的办法是将他们种在能开花的地方。

trans: 股东年会；年度股东大会

rootsaffixes.indicate: = year, one year 年, 一年
rootsaffixes.title: ann(u), enn

partsOfSpeech.dec: ann 年，一年 + al 表人或物 + s → 一年年的人和事物 → 编年史
anni〔= ann〕年，一年 + vers 转 + ary 物 → 一年转到一次 → 周年纪念
annu 年，一年 + al …的 → 一年一度的
annu 年，一年 + ity 具备某种性质，状况 → 每年都有的东西 → 年金
bi 二 + annu 年，一年 + al …的，具有…性质的 → 一年两次的
bi 二 + enn 年，一年 + ial …的 → 两年〔一次〕的
mill 千 + enn 年，一年 + ium → 一千年
per 自始至终 + enn 年，一年 + ial 具有…的，属于…的 → 一年到头 → 终年的
